pingze — data provenance
=========================

The source code in this repository is original work, licensed under the MIT
License (see LICENSE).

The linguistic data files under data/ are DERIVED from third-party open data and
classical reference works:

* data/phonology.tsv  and  data/cipu.dat
  Reprocessed (re-tagged, compacted, and re-encoded) from:
    charlesix59/chinese_word_rhyme
    https://github.com/charlesix59/chinese_word_rhyme
  which itself digitises the classical rime books and prosody manuals:
    《平水韵》   (Píngshuǐ rimes, the 106-rime standard for 近体诗)
    《词林正韵》 (Cílín Zhèngyùn, the 19-部 rhyme standard for 词)
    《钦定词谱》 (Qīndìng Cípǔ, the imperial register of 词 metrical patterns)
  augmented with the 定格/变格 templates from 龙榆生《唐宋词格律》.

* data/corrections.tsv
  Original: a small overlay of corrections to the upstream phonology table,
  found by validating against canonical rhyming poems.

These classical works are in the public domain. The upstream dataset is used
under its own license; please consult the linked repository for its terms.
